obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (72819)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72819&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called The Sugar Export Promotion Act, 1958.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (72820)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72820&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "export" means taking out of India by sea, land or air;`
  line
  line `(b) "export agency" means any such agency as may be specified in this behalf under section 3, and`
  line `when no such agency has been so specified, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) "export quota" means the export quota referred to in section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) "factory" means any premises (including the precincts thereof) wherein sugar is being produced`
  line `by the vacuum pan process;`
  line
  line `(e) "owner"--`
  line
  line `(i) with reference to any factory the possession of which has been transferred by lease, mortgage`
  line `or otherwise, means the transferee so long as his right to possession subsists;`
  line
  line `(ii) with reference to any factory for which an agent, by whatever name called, is employed,`
  line `means the agent, if, and in so far as, he has been duly authorised by the owner in that behalf, and`
  line
  line `(iii) with reference to any factory the management of which has been taken over by any person`
  line `or body of persons under the Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951),`
  line `means that person or body of persons;`
  line
  line `(f) "sugar" means any form of sugar containing more than ninety per cent, of sucrose;`
  line
  line `(g) "year" means the year beginning on the first day of May.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (72821)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Export agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72821&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify as an export agency any company within the meaning of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), or any body of persons established or recognised as a body corporated by or under any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such company or other body corporate has been specified as an export agency, it shall`
  line `be lawful for such agency to perform all or any of the functions of an export agency under this Act,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the memorandum or article of association of the`
  line `company or, as the case may be, the law applicable thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (72822)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Fixation of quantity of sugar for purposes of export.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72822&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, fix from time to time the quantity of sugar which may be exported`
  line `during any period, and, in fixing such quantity, the Central Government shall have regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the quantity of sugar available in India,`
  line
  line `(b) the quantity of sugar which, in its opinion, would be reasonably required for consumption in`
  line India,
  line
  line `(c) the necessity for exporting sugar with a view to earning foreign exchange in the public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) The power conferred by sub-section (1) shall be so exercised as to ensure that the quantity fixed`
  line `under that sub-section for any year does not exceed in the aggregate twenty per cent, of the quantity of`
  line `sugar produced in India in the season ending with the month of October falling within that year`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (72823)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Export quotas for factories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72823&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall by order in writing, apportion the`
  line `quantity of sugar fixed from time to time for purposes of export under section 4 among the owners in`
  line `proportion to the quantity of sugar produced, or likely to be produced, by them respectively during the`
  line `season referred to in sub-section (2) of section 4, and such order shall be communicated to each of the`
  line `owners, and the quantity so apportioned shall be deemed to be the export quota for the factory of that`
  line owner
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (72824)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Liability of owner to deliver export quota to export agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72824&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner shall, on demand`
  line `by the export agency, deliver to it from time to time sugar produced in his factory in such quantities (not`
  line `exceeding in the aggregate his export quota fixed for the factory or group of factories, as the case may`
  line `be), of such grade, in such manner, within such time and at such place, as may be specified by the export`
  line `agency in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) When sugar has been delivered by an owner in accordance with the provision of sub-section (1),`
  line `the owner shall retain no rights in respect of such sugar except his right to receive payment therefore`
  line `under section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (72825)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Levy of additional excise duty on sugar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs by Act 38 of 1960, s. 8, for “ seventeen rupees per mound” (w.e.f. 1-10-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72825&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where sugar delivered by any owner falls short of`
  line `the export quota fixed for it by any quantity (hereinafter referred to as the said quantity), there shall be`
  line `levied and collected on so much of the sugar dispatched from the factory for consumption in India as is`
  line `equal to the said quantity, a duty of excise at the rate of ^1[forty-five rupees and fifty five naye paise per`
  line quintal].
  line
  line `(2) The duty of excise referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in addition to the duty of excise`
  line `chargeable on sugar under any other law for the time being in force, and shall be paid by the owner to`
  line `such authority as may be specified in the notice demanding the payment of duty and within such period`
  line `not exceeding ninety days as may be specified in such notice.`
  line `person is liable under the rules made under the Central Excises and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944),`
  line `is adjudged.`
  line
  line `(3) If any such owner does not pay the whole or any part of the duty payable by him within the period`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2), he shall be liable to pay in respect of every period of thirty days or part`
  line `thereof during which the default continues a penalty which may extend to ten per cent, of the duty`
  line `outstanding from time to time, the penalty being adjudged in the same manner as the penalty to which a`
  line `forty-five rupees and fifty five naye paise per`
  line quintal.
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Central Excises and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, including those relating to refunds and exemptions from duty, shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to the levy and collection of the duty of excise or any other sum referred to in this section as they`
  line `apply in relation to the levy and collection of the duty on sugar or other sums of money payable to the`
  line `Central Government under that Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (72826)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Sale by export agency of sugar delivered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72826&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The export agency shall take all practical`
  line `measures to export sugar delivered to it under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the export agency is of opinion that having regard to the quality of the sugar delivered`
  line `to it by any owner, or to the expenses involved in transporting the sugar from one place to another, or to`
  line `the delay likely to be involved in exporting it, or to the conditions prevailing in the markets for sugar,`
  line `whether in or out of India, or to any other relevant circumstances, it is expedient so to do, the export`
  line `agency may sell the whole or any part of the sugar in India and may, if it thinks fit, purchase such`
  line `quantity of sugar as it may consider necessary for export at the appropriate time.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the export agency may itself sell sugar or permit the owner to`
  line `sell the whole or any part of the export quota in his custody at a price approved by it on condition that the`
  line `sale-proceeds are payable to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (72827)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payments to owners in respect of sugar delivered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72827&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The export agency shall, at such time as`
  line `it thinks fit, make to the owners who have delivered sugar to it under this Act, payments determined in`
  line `accordance with the provisions hereinafter in this section contained.`
  line
  line `(2) From the total sale proceeds in respect of the quantity fixed for export under section 4 for any year,`
  line `there shall be deducted the total expenditure incurred by the export agency in respect of the sugar,`
  line `whether by way of administrative expenses or otherwise, and the balance shall be apportioned among the`
  line `owners in proportion to the quantity of sugar delivered by them respectively during that year.`
  line
  line `(3) In making any distribution under this section, the export agency shall make such adjustments as`
  line `may be necessary having regard to the grade of sugar delivered by any owner, the adjustments being`
  line `made on the basis of sugar of ISS-E-29 grade and with reference to the price differential schedule for`
  line `different grades of sugar which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `publish in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section and subject to the rules which may be made in`
  line `this behalf, the export agency may make on account payments to owners against documents of delivery of`
  line `sugar furnished by them, and such payments shall be adjusted at the time of final payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (72828)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72828&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The export agency specified under`
  line `section 3 shall be bound, in the discharge of its functions under this Act, by such general or special`
  line `directions, as the Central Government may give to it in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (72829)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72829&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct, that any power conferred on it by this Act shall, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the notification, be exercisable also by such officer or authority subordinate to the Central`
  line `Government as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (72830)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Protection of action taken under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72830&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the export agency of the Central Government or any of its officers for or in respect of anything`
  line `which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (72831)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72831&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the submission by owners to such authority as may be specified in this behalf, of returns or`
  line `reports or other information relating to the manufacture, sale, dispatch, stocks and prices of sugar.`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the accounts of the export agency may be maintained and audited;`
  line
  line `(c) the inspection of records and registers of factories and the export agency;`
  line
  line `(d) the making of payments by the export agency to owners;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) In making a rule under this section, the Central Government may direct that a breach thereof shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules made under this Act shall be laid for not less than thirty days before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after they are made and shall be subject to such modifications as Parliament`
  line `may make during the session in which they are so laid or the session immediately following.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (72832)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337&sectionId=72832&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00121_195830_1675935991337
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `[Repealed by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1960 (58 of`
  line `1960), s. 2 and Sch. I.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
